page.title: 01FENSTANTON AREA
page.content: The parishes of{Fenstanton}and {Hemingford}are mainly fields.With {Fenstanton}in the east and{Hemingford in the north-west.Along the{A604}are many disused pits.It runs from the north-west to the south-east.There are quite a lot of drains because it is flat,wet fenland.Alongside{Fenstanton bypass there are a few farms.Most of the fields have brooks or drains near them.They contain wheat,corn,rape and barley.By the{Fenstanton golf range are some fruit trees,but only a few trees are scattered around the whole area.{Fenstanton}is mainly buildings but{Hemingford}has fewer.Near the {Whippet Depot}there is a bridge which leads to{St.Ives and Papworth. The{A604 Fenstanton bypass}gives access to{Huntingdon,Godmanchester one way and{Cambridge}and the{M11}the other way.
